Anne McGeorge



















Anne M. McGeorge
National Managing Partner, Health Care 

 Charlotte, NC



                            T
                        
                        +1 704 632 3520
                        
anne.mcgeorge@us.gt.com 








Print


Email





Facbook
















Executive summary
Anne McGeorge is a Tax Services partner and national managing partner of Grant Thornton’s Health Care practice. McGeorge is responsible for overseeing the service offerings to health care clients around the country, including audit, tax, valuation, reimbursement assistance, internal controls consulting, security risk consulting, litigation support, M&A, compensation consulting, SOX compliance, and other health care compliance. She has represented health care clients for more than 25 years and has worked extensively with large health systems, academic medical centers, community hospitals, managed care organizations, Blue Cross Blue Shield organizations, coalitions and purchasing organizations, and physician practices.

McGeorge has assisted clients in all aspects of financial consulting, including M&A, joint ventures, corporate restructuring, physician contracting, executive compensation, risk assessments, regulatory issues and IRS matters. She was formerly a partner with Deloitte & Touche and Arthur Andersen. McGeorge was selected as a “Woman Extraordinaire” by Business Leader magazine in 2011 and named one of Charlotte’s “Most Influential Women” in 2010 by the Mecklenburg Times.




