lly contacted Victory both Heather and Erick were there each step of the way, regardless of the hour or day. After a few short months, it was determined that I was NOT a liable party . It was such a blessing to my wife and me to know that we would no longer have to worry about paying $500,000 and we could finally move on with our life. We could not have done this without Victory, Heather or Erick. They by far are the most impressive group of professionals we have ever had the pleasure of working with. They saved us from declaring bankruptcy and allowed us to have our life back. We will always be grateful for what they have done for us. We thank the Victory team and thank God for leading us to Victory!  Blessings,J & J Victory Tax SolutionsJeff T. ratedVictory Tax Solutions gave us our life back!In 2005 through 2009 I was employed with a company based out of Virginia. In 2007 the company had fallen behind on their federal employment taxes exceeding $1M. In 2008-2009 I had a surgery that went awry and spent 43 days in ICU and had 18 follow-up surgeries. During this time the company had pointed the finger towards me and the IRS held me as a liable party for over $500,000 in back taxes for the company debt. I never had an opportunity to even appeal the case due to my health. I had obtained legal counsel to appeal this case in 2010 and was told there was nothing that could be done. After spending $4,000 in legal fees, I still remained a liable party. We were at a dead end and did not know what we were going to do. My wife and I came home one evening only to find a packet from the IRS threatening to garnish our wages for a debt that was not even ours. I immediately submitted an on-line request to Victory Tax Solutions. I thought due to the late hour I would not receive a call until the next day. To my surprise, I received a call from Erik Finkiewicz immediately. Within a couple days Victory started working on our case and I started working with one of Victory’s attorney’s