allments to get started. All the paperwork was submitted to me to sign within days of my first installment so they could get started working on my case. After the second payment, Terrance gave me a call the very next business day along with an attorney and explained to me how my case would go and what I could expect. I have $20,000 in tax debt between the two agencies and Victory Tax Solutions will be able to bring that to ZERO!!!! I am so grateful that I heard their advertisement and took the time to call. They have been on top of every thing since I contacted them a month ago. I am also impressed in how quickly they processed my case. If it hadn't been for me getting paid every two weeks I would have seen results in a matter of weeks. Thank you Victory Tax Solutions for all your hard work and for caring for those of us who are trying to get our lives back on track.Victory Tax SolutionsRichard S. ratedI received a lock-in letter from the IRS and if it would have been implemented, it would have created a huge hardship on me and my family. I can honestly say, it was one of the most stressful situations I've experienced. I knew that I had to do something, but didn't have the know how on how to dispute this. Furthermore, my past experiences with trying to work with the IRS have not been successful. So, I looked online and came across Victory Tax Solutions. I first talked to Matt who was very helpful in gathering up my information and explaining to me what to expect and the pricing. After my information was gathered, I was then told I would be working with their attorney Lyle. I wasn't sure what to expect because I've never really had any good experiences with attorneys. I've always found them to be easily annoyed with questions. Not the case with Lyle. He went above and beyond in making sure I understood exactly what was going on and made sure he answered all my questions. Lyle explained to me what was going to happen and the estimated time frame. I received some furth